[Nouns] unsavoriness; amaritude; acrimony, acridity; roughness (sour) [more]; acerbity, austerity; gall and wormwood, rue, quassia, aloes; marah; sickener.
[Verbs] be unpalatable; sicken, disgust, nauseate, pall, turn the stomach.
[Adjectives] unsavory, unpalatable, unsweet; ill-flavored; bitter, bitter as gall; acrid, acrimonious; rough.
offensive, repulsive, nasty; sickening; nauseous; loathsome, fulsome; unpleasant [more].
